name: Chicken Etouffee
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cayenne pepper'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup unsalted', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'extra-virgin olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'skinless, boneless chicken breasts, cubed'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'stalks', 'name': 'celery, chopped, or more to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'green bell pepper, chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'onion, chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'clove', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons unsalted', 'name': 'butter, or more to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'water, or as needed to cover'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': '', 'name': 'bay leaves'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'cooked rice'}
steps: Whisk flour, salt, black pepper, and cayenne pepper together in a bowl; add cubed chicken and dredge to coat. Reserve remaining seasoned flour.. Heat 1/4 cup butter and olive oil in a large skillet; add chicken and cook until golden brown and no longer pink inside, about 10 minutes. Transfer to a bowl, leaving butter mixture in skillet. Reduce heat to low.. Stir 1 tablespoon reserved seasoned flour into pan drippings; cook and stir until mixture forms a paste and dark caramel color, 10 to 15 minutes. Watch carefully and stir constantly to avoid burning. Add celery, bell pepper, onion, garlic, and remaining 2 tablespoons butter to flour paste; toss to coat with butter and browned flour mixture. Cook and stir until vegetables soft, about 10 minutes.. Add water to cover vegetables; add bay leaves and bring to a simmer. Return chicken to skillet; cook until flavors blended, about 10 minutes more. Serve with cooked rice.

name: Cajun Crawfish and Shrimp Étouffée
ingredients: {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'small', 'name': 'green bell pepper, diced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'medium', 'name': 'onion, chopped'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'stalks', 'name': 'celery, diced'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'medium', 'name': 'fresh tomatoes, chopped'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'Louisiana-style hot sauce'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cayenne pepper (Optional)'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'seafood seasoning'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'fish stock'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'crawfish tails'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'medium shrimp, peeled and deveined'}
steps: Heat the oil in a heavy skillet over medium heat. Gradually stir in flour, and stir constantly until the mixture turns 'peanut butter' brown or darker, at least 15 or 20 minutes. I use a large fork with the flat side to the bottom of the pan in a side to side motion. This is your base sauce or 'roux'. It is very important to stir this constantly. If by chance the roux burns, discard and start over.. Once the roux is browned, add the onions, garlic, celery and bell pepper to the skillet, and saute for about 5 minutes to soften. Stir in the chopped tomatoes and fish stock, and season with the seafood seasoning. Reduce heat to low, and simmer for about 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.. Season the sauce with hot pepper sauce and cayenne pepper (if using), and add the crawfish and shrimp. Cook for about 10 minutes, or until the shrimp are opaque.

name: Crawfish Etouffee IV
ingredients: {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'margarine'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'diced onion'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'diced green bell pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'minced garlic'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'peeled crawfish'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': '(10.75 ounce) cans', 'name': 'condensed cream of mushroom soup'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(10 ounce) can', 'name': 'diced tomatoes with green chile peppers'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'dried parsley'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt to taste'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'ground black pepper to taste'}
steps: In an 8 quart stock pot over medium heat, add vegetable oil and margarine. Saute onions, green pepper and garlic until onions are translucent.. Add crawfish to the onion mixture, and cook for 5 minutes. Add a little water to keep crawfish moist while cooking.. Stir in soup and diced tomatoes. Bring to a boil and simmer for 30 minutes. Sprinkle in parsley after about 10 minutes. Salt and pepper to taste while simmering. Water can be added to thin as desired.

name: Go-To Crawfish Etouffee
ingredients: {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'onion, diced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'green bell pepper, chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'bunch', 'name': 'green onions, chopped'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'stalks', 'name': 'celery, chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(10.75 ounce) can', 'name': 'condensed golden mushroom soup'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped fresh parsley'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'Cajun seasoning, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt and ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'crawfish tail meat'}
steps: Melt the butter in a large, heavy skillet over medium heat, and stir in the onion, green bell pepper, green onions, and celery; cook the vegetables, stirring frequently, until the onion is translucent and the vegetables have begun to soften, about 10 minutes. Stir in the golden mushroom soup, parsley, Cajun seasoning, salt, and black pepper, and bring the sauce to a boil.. Gently mix in the crawfish tail meat, and simmer until the crawfish tails are opaque, 10 to 15 minutes.

name: Heather's Crawfish Etouffee
ingredients: {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'long-grain white rice'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'margarine'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'onion, chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'medium', 'name': 'green bell pepper, chopped'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(10.5 ounce) can', 'name': 'condensed cream of mushroom soup'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'water, or as needed'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'cayenne pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'peeled crawfish tails'}
steps: Combine 4 cups water and rice in a saucepan; bring to a boil. Cover; reduce heat to low. Simmer until rice is tender and water has been absorbed, 15 to 20 minutes.. While rice is cooking, melt margarine in a large skillet over medium heat. Add onion and bell pepper; cook and stir until tender, 10 to 15 minutes. Stir in garlic; cook 1 minute.. Add cream of mushroom soup and 1/2 cup water to skillet; stir to combine. Season with salt, black pepper, and cayenne pepper; stir in crawfish tails. Cover and reduce heat to low; simmer for 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add water to thin sauce as needed. Serve over rice.

name: Crawfish Étouffée Like Maw-Maw Used to Make
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'onions, minced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'green bell pepper, diced'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, diced'}, {'quantity': '16', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'cleaned crawfish tails'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'water, or as needed'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cumin'}, {'quantity': '⅛', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'Worcestershire sauce'}, {'quantity': '⅛', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'hot sauce'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt and pepper to taste'}
steps: In a stockpot, melt butter over medium heat until bubbling. Add flour to make a roux, stirring constantly to prevent or remove any lumps. Cook the roux for 5 minutes. Do not brown.. Stir in onions and bell peppers; sauté for 10 minutes, or until onions are translucent. Add garlic and sauté for 3 minutes. Stir in crawfish tails. Slowly pour in enough water to reach a consistency that's a little thicker than soup. Season with cumin, Worcestershire sauce, hot sauce, salt, and pepper. Reduce the heat and simmer for 10 minutes.

name: Catfish Etouffee
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'enriched white rice'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'brown roux'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped onion'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped green bell pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'minced garlic'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'beef broth'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'tomatoes, coarsely chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'lemon juice'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'Worcestershire sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'bay leaf'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'dried thyme'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'catfish fillets, cut into 1 inch pieces'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped fresh parsley'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'red pepper flakes (to taste)'}
steps: Combine rice and water in a small saucepan. Bring to a boil, reduce heat to low, and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes, or until done.. In a large saucepan, warm roux over medium heat. Stir in onion, green bell pepper, and garlic; cook for about 5 minutes, or until soft. Stir in broth and tomatoes. Season with lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, bay leaf, black pepper, thyme, and salt. Reduce heat to low, cover, and simmer for 30 minutes.. Stir in catfish and parsley. Simmer, partially covered, for 10 minutes, or until fish flakes easily with a fork.. Stir in 2 cups cooked white rice, and season with red pepper flakes. Serve.

name: Microwave Shrimp Étouffée
ingredients: {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped onion'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped green onion'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped green bell pepper'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'minced garlic'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'celery, diced'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped fresh parsley'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'tomato paste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(10.5 ounce) can', 'name': 'condensed cream of chicken soup'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'cleaned shrimp'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt to taste'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'hot pepper sauce to taste'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'cayenne pepper'}
steps: In a 2-quart microwave safe dish, combine butter, onion, green onion, bell pepper, garlic and celery. Heat on High settings for 8 to 9 minutes.. Stir in parsley, tomato paste, soup, shrimp, salt, hot pepper sauce and cayenne. Heat on High setting for 5 minutes. Stir and cook for another 5 minutes until mixture thickens. Serve over white rice.

name: Ann's Shrimp Etouffee
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'white onions, chopped'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'stalks', 'name': 'celery, chopped'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, pressed'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '5', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'fresh shrimp, peeled, deveined and chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped fresh mushrooms'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'paprika'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt to taste'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'crushed red pepper to taste'}
steps: In a large skillet, melt butter and saute onions, celery and garlic for about 45 minutes or until they are cooked down.. Stir in flour and cook briefly, do not brown. Stir in chopped shrimp and cook for 20 minutes.. Pour in 2 to 3 cups of water and mushrooms. Stir in paprika and season with salt, pepper and red pepper flakes. Cook for 30 minutes. Should be a thick and have a gravy-like consistency.

name: Tammi's Crawfish Etoufee
ingredients: {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sliced fresh mushrooms'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'frozen raw crawfish'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped green onion'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'minced fresh parsley'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'half-and-half'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'crushed red pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'Creole-style seasoning'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt to taste'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'ground black pepper to taste'}
steps: In a large skillet over medium heat, heat butter and olive oil together. Saute garlic powder and mushrooms until mushrooms are tender; about 3 to 5 minutes.. Add crawfish and onions. Reduce heat to low and cook for 5 minutes.. Stir in Parmesan cheese, parsley, and half and half. Simmer for 5 minutes and stir in crushed red pepper and Creole seasoning. Salt and pepper to taste.

name: Catfish Étouffée
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped onion'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped green bell pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped celery'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(14.5 ounce) can', 'name': 'diced tomatoes'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'low-sodium chicken broth'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'Louisiana-style hot sauce'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'dried thyme, crushed'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'Worcestershire sauce'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'catfish, cut into 6 pieces'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'chopped fresh parsley'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'cooked riced cauliflower'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sliced green onion'}
steps: Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add onion, green pepper, and celery; cook until vegetables are just beginning to soften, about 7 minutes. Add tomatoes, broth, hot sauce, thyme, Worcestershire, salt, and black pepper. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium-low; simmer, uncovered, until thickened and saucy, about 15 minutes.. Put catfish pieces on top of the vegetable mixture. Cook, covered, until catfish is just cooked through and opaque, about 10 minutes.. Remove catfish from the skillet and keep warm. Stir parsley into skillet. Serve étouffée and catfish over riced cauliflower. Sprinkle with green onion.

name: Shrimp Etoufee III
ingredients: {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'fresh shrimp, peeled and deveined'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'crushed red pepper flakes'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'margarine, divided'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'minced onion'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'sliced celery'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'diced green bell pepper'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'cornstarch'}, {'quantity': '3 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'water'}
steps: In a large bowl, combine the shrimp, salt, pepper, and red pepper flakes. Blend well. Cover and place in the refrigerator.. In a large pot over medium heat, melt 1/2 cup of margarine and add the onions. Saute the onions until they are translucent.. Stir in the celery and bell pepper. Increase the heat to high and stir occasionally for 20 minutes. Add the remaining 1/2 cup of margarine and bring to a boil. Fold in the shrimp and reduce heat to medium cook for 10 minutes.. Mix the cornstarch and water together and slowly pour it into the pot; just covering the top of the shrimp mixture. Cook on medium/high heat until the celery is soft; about 20 minutes. Add any additional salt, pepper and red pepper flakes to taste.
